  {
    "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
    "body": "This is a complicated edge case, a bit of a chicken-and-egg problem.\r\n\r\n1. createURL called by the widget is createURL called by the connector\r\n2. the result of createURL depends on what the current UI state + mounted widgets is\r\n3. when you call createURL, in an initial render (like on server side rendering) the widgets aren't yet mounted\r\n\r\nThis problem also happens when you aren't doing server side rendering, but as the second render is right after the first one, it never commits the incomplete URL.\r\n\r\nAt this point I'm not yet sure what the solution would be.\r\n\r\nEDIT: I believe I found an option which would still need to be polished if it proves to work, see #5408, which you can try via codesandbox if you feel like it :)\r\nEDIT2: that approach doesn't work in all cases, we'd need to find something else",
    "created_at": "2023-01-03T11:43:36Z",
