  {
    "author_association": "NONE",
    "body": "@Haroenv \r\n\r\nWe are using NextJS with SSR and ran into this issue when implementing `useRefinementList`. To improve our SEO, we want to render links for each filter (but default to client side navigation once JS loads). We are blocked because `createURL` only runs on the client.\r\n\r\n> This is a complicated edge case, a bit of a chicken-and-egg problem.\r\n> \r\n> 1. createURL called by the widget is createURL called by the connector\r\n> 2. the result of createURL depends on what the current UI state + mounted widgets is\r\n> 3. when you call createURL, in an initial render (like on server side rendering) the widgets aren't yet mounted\r\n\r\nIs this actually a limitation when running `InstantSearchSSRProvider` ([docs](https://www.algolia.com/doc/api-reference/widgets/ssr-provider/react-hooks/))?\r\n\r\nI'm running `getServerState` ([docs](https://www.algolia.com/doc/api-reference/widgets/server-state/react-hooks/)) in `getServerSideProps` _before_ SSR begins. At this point, we don't care if `createURL` returns nothing. At the next stage, we begin SSR knowing the UI state. Why can't `createURL` know the correct URL?",
    "created_at": "2023-05-29T02:41:12Z",
    "html_url": "https://github.com/algolia/instantsearch/issues/5236#issuecomment-1566414241",
